-- Romania Stocks Fall Most in 3 Months as Prime Minister Resigns
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-06T10:37:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/romania-stocks-fall-most-in-3-months-as-prime-minister-resigns.html
Romanian stocks slumped the most in
three months after Prime Minister Emil Boc said he will resign.  The benchmark BET  index  of shares fell 2.3 percent to
4,888.46 by 12:24 p.m. in Bucharest, the biggest intraday drop
since Nov. 1.  OMV Petrom SA (SNP) ,  Romania ’s largest oil company,
plunged 3.2 percent and  Banca Transilvania SA (TLV) , the country’s
second-largest publicly traded bank, fell 2.5 percent.  Boc announced today in a televised speech during a
government briefing in Bucharest that he quit to “ease
political and social pressures in the country” and let another
government continue reforms. President Traian Basescu named
Justice Minister Catalin Predoiu as interim premier, according
to a statement on his website.  Romania’s leu snapped two days of gains, depreciating 0.1
percent to 4.3435 per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
